Dippi is a simple application which analyzes any display. Inputs a
few simple details and figures out the aspect ratio, DPI, and
other details of a particular display.
Great for deciding which laptop or external monitor to purpose, and
if it would be considered HiDPI.

Handy features:
* Find out if a display is a good choice based on its size and resolution
* Get advice about different densities
* Learn the logical resolution
* Differentiate between laptops and desktop displays

WWW: https://github.com/cassidyjames/dippi
